  <h2>Liver Support</h2>
  <p>The liver is the body’s primary detox organ, central to immune signaling and antigen clearance.</p>
  <ul class="bullets">
    <li>Processes xenobiotics, hormones, and inflammatory byproducts.</li>
    <li>Healthy liver function correlates with resilient immunity.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Key Liver-Supporting Nutrients with Strong Evidence</h3>
  <ul class="bullets">
    <li><strong>Curcumin</strong> (from turmeric) — antioxidant and anti-inflammatory actions; researched in NAFLD/NASH contexts <sup>11</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29151096/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
    <li><strong>Green Tea Catechins</strong> — EGCG and related catechins studied for liver fat and inflammation modulation <sup>9</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24366029/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
    <li><strong>Dandelion Root</strong> — traditional choleretic; emerging data on hepatoprotective effects <sup>10</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19919579/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
    <li><strong>Milk Thistle</strong> (silymarin) — long-studied hepatoprotective complex with antioxidant activity <sup>8</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21334871/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h4 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-top: 1rem;">Other Liver Supporting Research Worth Mentioning</h4>
  <ul class="bullets">
    <li><strong>Vitamin E</strong> — RCTs in non-diabetic NASH; pediatric benefit in TONIC trial <sup>12</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20427778/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
    <li><strong>Coffee</strong> — meta-analyses associate intake with lower fibrosis risk and improved outcomes in chronic liver disease <sup>13</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28699464/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
    <li><strong>Omega-3 fatty acids</strong> (n-3 PUFAs) — trials show liver fat reduction and lipid improvements in NAFLD <sup>14</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29191773/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
    <li><strong>Artichoke Leaf Extract</strong> — RCTs: reductions in ALT/AST and ultrasound markers of fatty liver <sup>15</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26196153/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
    <li><strong>N-acetylcysteine (NAC)</strong> — studied for oxidative stress reduction and transaminase improvements <sup>16</sup>. <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24206429/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Study</a></li>
  </ul>

