    <p>
      The liver is your body’s main detox powerhouse — filtering blood, metabolizing nutrients, and neutralizing toxins. Cleansing (as described before) helps reduce the toxic load on this vital organ, but cleansing alone is not enough. To truly support the liver, it must also be nourished with the nutrients it needs to repair, regenerate, and operate its many functions at peak efficiency. Supplying the liver with targeted vitamins, minerals, and plant compounds — with specific foods, teas, and powerful antioxidants (as found in fruits like wolfberries) — has been shown in scientific studies to provide liver-protective effects<sup>1-3</sup>, improve antioxidant status<sup>4,5</sup>, and reduce oxidative stress<sup>6,7</sup>.  
      In addition to nutrient-rich fruits, certain herbal teas have also demonstrated strong liver-supportive properties. Milk thistle tea, rich in silymarin, has been shown to protect liver cells and promote regeneration<sup>8</sup>. Green tea catechins have demonstrated antioxidant and anti-inflammatory benefits for the liver<sup>9</sup>, while dandelion root tea supports bile production and overall liver detoxification<sup>10</sup>.
    </p>
